          "question": "Differentiate $y = \\frac{5x}{x+1}$ with respect to $x$.",
          "options": [
            "$\\frac{5}{(x+1)^2}$",
            "$\\frac{5x+5-5x}{x+1}$",
            "$\\frac{5}{x+1}$",
            "$\\frac{10x+5}{(x+1)^2}$"
          ],
          "correct_option": "A",
          "explanation": "Quotient rule with $u=5x$, $v=x+1$: $\\frac{dy}{dx} = \\frac{5(x+1) - 5x}{(x+1)^2} = \\frac{5}{(x+1)^2}$.",
          "diagram_required": "none"
