        {
          "question_format": "mcq",
          "question": "Find the equation of the tangent to the curve $y = \\frac{e^{\\frac{1}{3}x}}{x}$ at the point $\\left(3, \\frac{1}{3}e\\right)$.",
          "options": [
            "$y = \\frac{1}{3}e$",
            "$y = \\frac{1}{3}ex$",
            "$y - \\frac{1}{3}e = \\frac{1}{3}e(x-3)$",
            "$y = 0$"
          ],
          "correct_option": "A",
          "explanation": "Quotient rule gives $\\frac{dy}{dx} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{3}e^{x/3}\\cdot x - e^{x/3}}{x^2}$. At $x=3$: $\\frac{e - e}{9} = 0$. Gradient is zero, so the tangent is the horizontal line $y = \\frac{1}{3}e$.",
          "diagram_required": "none"
        }
      ]
    },
