        {
          "question_format": "mcq",
          "question": "Given $f(x) = \\frac{2x}{x+5} + \\frac{6x}{x^2+7x+10}$, find $f'(3)$.",
          "options": [
            "0.16",
            "4",
            "0.64",
            "1.5"
          ],
          "correct_option": "A",
          "explanation": "Factorise: $x^2+7x+10=(x+5)(x+2)$. Combining gives $\\frac{2x(x+2)+6x}{(x+5)(x+2)} = \\frac{2x(x+5)}{(x+5)(x+2)} = \\frac{2x}{x+2}$. Then $f'(x) = \\frac{4}{(x+2)^2}$. At $x=3$: $f'(3) = \\frac{4}{25} = 0.16$.",
          "diagram_required": "none"
        }
      ]
    },
